    "John Trapp": "Take away sin ] Separando auferre, sunder it from the soul, strike a parting blow betwixt them, \u03c0\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03b5\u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03bd, Undique tollere.\nVer.\n11. Take away sin] Separando auferre, sunder it from the soul, strike a parting blow betwixt them, \u03c0\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03b5\u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03bd, Undique tollere.\nVer.\n11. A melancholy man can fancy vast and terrible fears, fire, sword, racks, strappadoes, scalding lead, boiling pitch, running bell metal, and this to all eternity; yet all these are nothing to that wrath of God which none can either avoid or abide.\nVer."
